@version 1
/// example: 096-hallmark-reserved-name
/// level: 2
/// concept: a hallmark cannot mint a reserved name — a built-in type, a currency/unit tag, or a governance term
/// expected_diagnostics: FUNGI-HALLMARK-001
/// test_status: stable
/// ai_rule: Names carry no authority; Money/Verdict/GBP and other reserved names cannot be minted as hallmarks.

// Minting 'Money' would let a developer shadow the built-in financial type and confuse
// its semantics — the protected-marks rule refuses it. The targeted hint steers you to
// Money<GBP> or a 'unit' declaration. (GBP, Verdict, Trusted, Secret, … are refused too.)
hallmark Money of Decimal {
  gate: flow assayMoney
}

pure flow assayMoney(raw: Decimal) -> Result<Decimal, ValidationError> {
  contract { intent "the mint is refused before this gate ever matters" }
  return Ok(raw)
}
